{"cursor":"12998","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\nA 'genetic screen' is an experimental technique used to identify and select for\nindividuals who possess a phenotype of interest in a mutagenized population. Hence a genetic screen is a type of phenotypic\nscreen. Genetic screens can provide important information on gene function as\nwell as the molecular events that underlie a biological process or pathway.\nWhile genome projects have identified an extensive inventory of genes in many\ndifferent organisms, genetic screens can provide valuable insight as to how\nthose genes function.\n","linknr":204,"url":"Positional_cloning","recorded":1362480565,"links":9,"instances":["biological","genetics","genetics"],"pdf":[],"categories":["Classical genetics","Molecular genetics","Medical genetics","Genetics experiments"],"headings":["Basic Screening","Screening variations","Mapping mutants","Positional cloning","External links","References"],"image":["//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4","//bits.wikimedia.org/images/wikimedia-button.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/poweredby_mediawiki_88x31.png"],"tags":[["trait","biological"],["transformation","genetics"],["polymorphism","biology#genetics"],["locus","genetics"]],"members":["trait","polymorphism","locus","transformation"],"related":["Phenotype","Phenotypic_screen","Gene","Genome_project","Forward_genetics","Reverse_genetics","Allele","Mutagen","Chromosome","Christiane_NÃ¼sslein-Volhard","Eric_Wieschaus","Suppressor_mutation","Temperature","Gene","Null_mutation","Lee_Hartwell","Paul_Nurse","Classical_genetics","Chromosome","Crossbreeding","Trait_(biological)","Allele","Single_nucleotide_polymorphism","Transformation_(genetics)","Transposable_elements","Genetic_marker","Candidate_gene","Linkage_analysis","Contig_map","Locus_(genetics)","Chromosome_walking","Human_Genome_Project","DNA_clone","Genetic_recombination","Wild_type","Mutant",